        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 5:22PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Markham, or near Bay City, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bay City, Van Vleck, and Markham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
